library(ggplot2)
setwd("/home/eeb177-student/Desktop/eeb-177/eeb177-final-project") #you will need to change this to match your directory!
cetacea <- read.csv("/home/eeb177-student/Desktop/eeb-177/eeb177-final-project/data_for_graphing", header = F, as.is = T)
names(cetacea) <- c("genus", "species", "minage", "maxage")
head(cetacea)
##           genus                      species   minage   maxage
## 1  Leptodelphis Leptodelphis stavropolitanus 12.15400 12.15400
## 2     Squalodon           Squalodon dalpiazi 14.89500 18.20500
## 3   Chilcacetus       Chilcacetus cavirhinus 21.73500 21.73500
## 4 Mycteriacetus    Mycteriacetus bellunensis 21.73500 21.73500
## 5    Aglaocetus          Aglaocetus burtinii  3.96050  9.43300
## 6   Indopacetus        Indopacetus pacificus  0.00585  0.00585
cetacea_occ <- ggplot(cetacea, aes( x = species, maxage, colour = genus))
# everything
cetacea_occ + geom_linerange(aes(ymin = minage, ymax = maxage)) + theme(legend.position="none") +  coord_flip() +  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(size=1)) + scale_y_continuous(limits=c(0, 50), expand = c(0, 0), breaks=c(0, 10, 20, 30, 40, 50)) + labs(title = "Cetacea Fossil Occurrences", x = "Species", y = "Ma ago") + theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size=22, face = "bold"), axis.title =element_text(size=20))

library(tidyr)
library(dplyr)
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
diversity <- cetacea %>% gather(key = type, value = age, minage, maxage) %>% mutate(count = ifelse(type == "maxage", 1, -1)) %>% group_by(age) %>% summarise(count = sum(count))  %>% arrange(-age, -count) %>% mutate(diversity = cumsum(count)) 
ggplot(diversity, aes(x = age, y = diversity)) + geom_step()
